    <etym xml:lang="ru">Н. W. %sBailey%s сближает с <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                    ><lang/><w>kṣāna-</w><gloss><q>плечевая
            лопатка</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                ><w/><gloss><q>scapula</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
                ><lang/><w>šānak</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><lang/><w>šānah</w><gloss><q>гребень</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>лопатка</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Значения, по нашему
        мнению, плохо вяжутся. Можно предполагать, что в основе лежит понятие „упряжки“. В этом
        случае %ifsonʒ%i можно возвести к %i*span-ti%i, с многочисленной родней в индоевропейских
        языках: <mentioned xml:lang="sr"><lang/><w>спона</w><gloss><q>пута
            лошади</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sr"
            ><w/><gloss><q>петля</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="cs"
                ><lang/><w>spona</w><gloss><q>скоба</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="cs"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>скрепа</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="be"
                ><lang/><w>спона</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>за-понь,
                су-понь</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/><w>pantis</w><gloss><q>путы
                    для скота</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lv"
                    ><lang/><w>spanda</w><gloss><q>веревка для привязывания плуга к
            ярму</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sqj"
                    ><lang/><w>pendε</w><gloss><q>упряжка из пары быков</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="de"
            ><lang/><w>Ge-spann</w><gloss><q>упряжка</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="de"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>запряжка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                ><w>spannen</w><gloss><q>натягивать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="de"><w/><gloss><q>запрягать</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="ang"
            ><lang/><w>spannan</w><gloss><q>запрягать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ang"><w/><gloss><q>прикреплять</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>vi-fšan-</w><gloss><q>разрывать</q></gloss></mentioned>.
        Идеосемантика слова %ifsonʒ%i была бы в этом случае такая же, как у общеиндоевропейского
        названия ярма (<mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>yuga-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>иго</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                ><lang/><w>ζυγόν</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"
            ><lang/><w>jugum</w></mentioned> от <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                    ><lang/><w>yug-</w><gloss><q>связывать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>соединять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>скреплять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>запрягать</q></gloss></mentioned>, ). Дигорская форма %iæfsoj%i —
        вторичная; ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fynʒ"/> | %ifij%i, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_ærcynʒ"/> | %iærcij%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lxyncʼ"/> |
                %iælxij%i.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"
        /><biblScope>36</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>54</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Н. W. %sBailey%s connects it with <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                ><lang/><w>kṣāna-</w><gloss><q>humeral scapula</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><w/><gloss><q>scapula</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>šānak</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>šānah</w><gloss><q>comb</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>scapula</q></gloss></mentioned>, . The meanings, in our opinion,
        do not fit well. It can be assumed that it is based on the concept ‘team (of horses)’. In
        this case %ifsonʒ%i can be traced back to %i*span-ti%i, with numerous correspondences in
        Indo-European languages: <mentioned xml:lang="sr"><lang/><w>спона</w><gloss><q>horse
                    fetter</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sr"
                ><w/><gloss><q>loop</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="cs"
                ><lang/><w>spona</w><gloss><q>staple</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="cs"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>clench</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="be"
                ><lang/><w>спона</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>за-понь,
                су-понь</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"
                    ><lang/><w>pantis</w><gloss><q>cattle fetter</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="lv"><lang/><w>spanda</w><gloss><q>rope for tying the plough to the
                yoke</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sqj"
                    ><lang/><w>pendε</w><gloss><q>team of a pair of bulls</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="de"
            ><lang/><w>Ge-spann</w><gloss><q>team</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="de"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>harness</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                ><w>spannen</w><gloss><q>stretch</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>harness</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ang"
                ><lang/><w>spannan</w><gloss><q>harness</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ang"><w/><gloss><q>attach</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>vi-fšan-</w><gloss><q>tear to pieces</q></gloss></mentioned>. The
        ideosemantics of the word %ifsonʒ%i would be in this case the same as of the common
        Indo-European yoke name (<mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>yuga-</w></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>иго</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                ><lang/><w>ζυγόν</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"
            ><lang/><w>jugum</w></mentioned> from <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                    ><lang/><w>yug-</w><gloss><q>tie together</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>join</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>fasten together</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>harness</q></gloss></mentioned>, ). Digor form %iæfsoj%i is
        secondary; cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fynʒ"/> | %ifij%i, <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_ærcynʒ"/> | %iærcij%i, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lxyncʼ"/> |
                %iælxij%i.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"
        /><biblScope>36</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                /><biblScope>54</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
